  "text": "On the other hand, for transport analysis of the highest power discharges for example, some chirping modes must be taken into account in the calculation of the ion and electron heating power. While only the neutron measurements have been used for calculating the effective diffusion coefficient (including the fission chamber and neutron camera [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ), a range of functional forms for the spatial/energy dependence of the diffusion coefficient may exist. In this respect the FIDA data may corroborate/invalidate some of these models.",
